2
00:00:01.500 --> 00:00:03.480
US, US

3
00:00:04.100 --> 00:00:09.340
US, ALL OF US

4
00:00:12.970 --> 00:00:15.770
The end of the dream, the end of the sea

5
00:00:15.770 --> 00:00:17.750
We all have different places we want to go We all have different places we want to go WE ALL HAVE DIFFERENT PLACES WE WANT TO GO

6
00:00:15.790 --> 00:00:18.530
We all have different places we want to go

7
00:00:18.530 --> 00:00:21.310
But to start we've got to show what we're made of

8
00:00:21.310 --> 00:00:25.660
We'll be legends, we're gonna take the world by storm

9
00:00:26.930 --> 00:00:29.250
Sparks are flying, NO LIMITS! This is where it starts

10
00:00:29.250 --> 00:00:30.530
ONE PIECE!!

11
00:00:30.890 --> 00:00:33.510
VORONOI START VORONOI END ALL OF US, I've got a question for you ALL OF US, I've got a question for you

12
00:00:33.510 --> 00:00:37.100
Have you let the world and all its burdens bring your dreams down?

13
00:00:38.740 --> 00:00:45.300
Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much

14
00:00:45.410 --> 00:00:52.030
Still we try, ALL OF US have our own paths we cling to

15
00:00:52.030 --> 00:00:54.620
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you

16
00:00:53.620 --> 00:00:55.150
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

17
00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:58.200
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

18
00:00:54.740 --> 00:00:58.050
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

19
00:00:59.890 --> 00:01:02.580
Random clues suddenly fit together

20
00:01:02.580 --> 00:01:06.510
Starting to make sense, oh, what's going on?

21
00:01:06.510 --> 00:01:12.980
Threads of time weaving into an intricate tapestry

22
00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:18.680
We can't stop the world from turning, it's changing along with every one of-

23
00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:21.250
US, US

24
00:01:21.870 --> 00:01:26.360
US, ALL OF US

25
00:01:30.110 --> 00:01:35.490
<b>Scrap Heap
Fabriophase
Egghead</b>

26
00:01:35.490 --> 00:01:37.950
So cool! Check it out, guys!

27
00:01:40.200 --> 00:01:41.500
I'm like Sanji!

28
00:01:41.500 --> 00:01:42.920
What happened to your head?!

29
00:01:42.920 --> 00:01:46.380
It's supposed to look like a giant light bulb!

30
00:01:47.500 --> 00:01:48.760
My head?

31
00:01:50.590 --> 00:01:53.180
It had grown quite a bit, so...

32
00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:54.090
I cut it.

33
00:01:54.090 --> 00:01:56.720
Don't say it like you got a haircut!

34
00:01:57.100 --> 00:02:03.690
Indeed, when last we met, I had
almost reached the height of a giant!

35
00:02:03.690 --> 00:02:06.650
I'd heard it was quite big...

36
00:02:06.650 --> 00:02:08.070
Like a hot air balloon.

37
00:02:09.900 --> 00:02:12.280
You trimmed down your
cranium without dying...

38
00:02:12.280 --> 00:02:14.280
How'd you pull it off?!

39
00:02:15.620 --> 00:02:18.160
You see, it's because...

40
00:02:19.240 --> 00:02:20.330
I'm a Brain-Brain-Brain-Brai–

41
00:02:20.790 --> 00:02:23.160
Ow, ow, ow... I bit my tongue...

42
00:02:23.160 --> 00:02:24.540
I bit... my tongue...

43
00:02:24.540 --> 00:02:26.750
Everything okay, gramps?

44
00:02:27.750 --> 00:02:30.460
You see, it's because...

45
00:02:30.960 --> 00:02:33.380
I'm a brain man who ate the Brain-Brain Fruit!

46
00:02:33.380 --> 00:02:36.550
There's no limit to what I can memorize,

47
00:02:36.550 --> 00:02:41.140
but my brain gets bigger and bigger
in proportion to the data capacity!

48
00:02:41.520 --> 00:02:46.060
A data bank of unlimited capacity
coupled with my inborn genius brain!

49
00:02:46.060 --> 00:02:51.690
It's now the largest brain
in the world and still growing!

50
00:02:51.690 --> 00:02:52.820
Still?

51
00:02:52.820 --> 00:02:54.150
Where is it?

52
00:02:54.150 --> 00:02:56.490
What are you even talking about?

53
00:02:59.450 --> 00:03:02.250
Gramps, if you cut your head,
are you stupid now?

54
00:03:02.250 --> 00:03:04.830
Don't question my scientific brilliance!

55
00:03:04.830 --> 00:03:06.670
This apple...

56
00:03:07.960 --> 00:03:09.250
is an antenna!

57
00:03:09.250 --> 00:03:10.750
That's an antenna?

58
00:03:10.750 --> 00:03:12.800
Look toward the top of the island…

59
00:03:14.970 --> 00:03:18.970
where “Punk Records” is
written within the giant egg!

60
00:03:19.850 --> 00:03:22.470
That's where I store my brain!

61
00:03:22.470 --> 00:03:23.730
What?!

62
00:03:23.730 --> 00:03:25.440
Isn't it too big?!

63
00:03:25.440 --> 00:03:31.270
I may be separated from it, but this antenna
can easily pick up my brain waves!

64
00:03:31.270 --> 00:03:33.110
That's incredible!

65
00:03:33.110 --> 00:03:36.450
Are you good at medicine,
too, Dr. Vegapunk?!

66
00:03:36.450 --> 00:03:37.780
Of course!

67
00:03:37.780 --> 00:03:39.780
Seriously?!

68
00:03:39.780 --> 00:03:44.290
Earlier, you folks met a girl who
called herself Vegapunk, correct?

69
00:03:46.410 --> 00:03:48.670
She punched me.

70
00:03:48.710 --> 00:03:52.590
She's one of my six clones who
work here on this island!

71
00:03:52.590 --> 00:03:53.710
You're a ninja too?!

72
00:03:53.710 --> 00:03:56.590
Can you use the clone technique?! Nin, nin!

73
00:03:59.300 --> 00:04:03.180
Each of them is an expert
in the fields I deem necessary!

74
00:04:03.600 --> 00:04:06.430
The levelheaded and fair Shaka!

75
00:04:06.480 --> 00:04:09.350
<b>AAAAAAAAAA</b>
<b>Shaka the Just</b>

76
00:04:09.810 --> 00:04:12.610
The wicked, plundering Lilith!

77
00:04:12.650 --> 00:04:15.530
<b>AAAAAAAAAAAAAA</b>
<b>Lilith the Evil</b>

78
00:04:15.530 --> 00:04:17.530
The inventor, Edison!

79
00:04:17.570 --> 00:04:20.450
<b>Edison the Visionary</b>
<b>AAAAAAAAAAAAAA</b>

80
00:04:20.450 --> 00:04:23.830
The wise, inquiring mind, Pythagoras!

81
00:04:23.870 --> 00:04:26.750
<b>Pythagoras the Wise</b>
<b>AAAAAAAAAAAAAA</b>

82
00:04:26.750 --> 00:04:29.620
The violent Atlas!

83
00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:32.540
<b>Atlas the Enraged</b>
<b>AAAAAAAAAAAAAA</b>

84
00:04:32.540 --> 00:04:35.880
Snack, dump, nap. The greedy York!

85
00:04:35.920 --> 00:04:38.800
<b>York the Greedy</b>
<b>AAAAAAAAAAAAAA</b>

86
00:04:38.800 --> 00:04:42.930
The six of them together
comprise my personality...

87
00:04:44.430 --> 00:04:47.270
but they make up six people's worth of work!

88
00:04:47.270 --> 00:04:49.350
What are you talking about?

89
00:04:49.350 --> 00:04:55.730
Once daily, they synchronize their experience
and knowledge via Punk Records.

90
00:04:55.730 --> 00:05:01.200
Their personalities and missions are different,
making each experience worthwhile!

91
00:05:03.240 --> 00:05:05.370
You all share the same brain?

92
00:05:05.370 --> 00:05:07.870
I'm not sure I understand it all.

93
00:05:07.870 --> 00:05:11.000
Just imagine we're all
accessing the same library.

94
00:05:14.960 --> 00:05:16.500
For example...

95
00:05:18.090 --> 00:05:23.340
if anyone in the world
could have access to my brain,

96
00:05:25.470 --> 00:05:29.480
it would be as if all humankind
had acquired my knowledge!

97
00:05:32.270 --> 00:05:37.570
Furthermore, if all of humanity could mutually
update Punk Records on a continual basis...

98
00:05:41.650 --> 00:05:47.370
the resulting sea of knowledge would
far surpass what I could accomplish alone!

99
00:05:49.500 --> 00:05:53.040
Humankind in its entirety can
someday share the same brain!

100
00:05:53.040 --> 00:05:56.170
You mean I can study medicine from all over the world?!

101
00:05:56.170 --> 00:05:57.800
Of course!

102
00:06:01.220 --> 00:06:03.380
I'm not sure I get it, but...

103
00:06:06.470 --> 00:06:10.520
But wouldn't it be problematic
if ideology were to creep in?

104
00:06:10.520 --> 00:06:13.100
Keenly observed, Jinbe, Knight of the Sea.

105
00:06:13.100 --> 00:06:15.940
But fretting over such things...

106
00:06:16.310 --> 00:06:18.770
halts the advance of science!

107
00:06:21.110 --> 00:06:24.240
That sort of thinking is the problem, Vegapunk!

108
00:06:24.240 --> 00:06:28.280
You don't care what sacrifices
are made in the name of science!

109
00:06:31.450 --> 00:06:32.870
That's why...

110
00:06:33.410 --> 00:06:36.210
you turned my father into
a soulless weapon of war!

111
00:06:37.750 --> 00:06:39.130
Stop, Bonney!

112
00:06:39.130 --> 00:06:41.380
That beam saber is a failure!

113
00:06:41.380 --> 00:06:44.510
Shut up! I've already tested it!

114
00:06:44.510 --> 00:06:46.260
Relax, Bonney!

115
00:06:46.260 --> 00:06:47.640
Use your head!

116
00:06:47.640 --> 00:06:52.140
Kill him, and you'll be making a lot of enemies!

117
00:06:52.140 --> 00:06:53.770
I don't care!

118
00:06:53.770 --> 00:06:56.520
Now, change my father back!

119
00:06:56.940 --> 00:06:59.610
If you say no...

120
00:07:01.570 --> 00:07:04.200
Turn off the switch, Bonney!

121
00:07:04.200 --> 00:07:05.950
That beam...

122
00:07:05.950 --> 00:07:06.740
Huh?

123
00:07:09.160 --> 00:07:10.200
What?

124
00:07:12.240 --> 00:07:15.460
...will attract a profuse number of insects!

125
00:07:26.300 --> 00:07:27.800
Hey!

126
00:07:27.800 --> 00:07:29.510
Wake up!

127
00:07:29.510 --> 00:07:30.760
Hey!

128
00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:32.260
Bonney!

129
00:07:34.020 --> 00:07:35.140
A big stag beetle!

130
00:07:35.140 --> 00:07:39.310
She just passed out, and all you care about
is some big freaking stag beetle?!

131
00:07:40.610 --> 00:07:44.690
I would've died had that weapon
not been a failure...

132
00:07:44.690 --> 00:07:46.150
But it's no wonder...

133
00:07:46.150 --> 00:07:47.700
No wonder...

134
00:07:47.700 --> 00:07:50.280
why Bonney wants to kill me.

135
00:07:51.410 --> 00:07:53.540
Oh! That's right...

136
00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:56.040
I heard you were in Wano until recently.

137
00:07:57.370 --> 00:07:58.250
Yeah.

138
00:07:58.250 --> 00:08:03.000
Is it true that another dragon
appeared besides Kaido?

139
00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:04.090
Yeah!

140
00:08:04.090 --> 00:08:05.840
That would be Momo!

141
00:08:07.880 --> 00:08:13.510
It sounds like that individual ate
a failed devil fruit I left at Punk Hazard.

142
00:08:13.510 --> 00:08:14.770
Oh, he did?

143
00:08:14.770 --> 00:08:17.100
Wait... Failed?

144
00:08:17.730 --> 00:08:21.980
It was a devil fruit that I had synthesized.

145
00:08:21.980 --> 00:08:25.740
To craft it using Kaido's hereditary elements,

146
00:08:25.740 --> 00:08:29.240
I spent twenty years and more
research money than you can count!

147
00:08:29.240 --> 00:08:32.700
However, I was unable to replicate
the fruit's composition.

148
00:08:32.700 --> 00:08:36.700
So that's why he could transform like Kaido!

149
00:08:36.700 --> 00:08:38.500
It worked great!

150
00:08:38.500 --> 00:08:40.370
He became strong and breathes fire!

151
00:08:40.370 --> 00:08:42.670
Now he's one of Wano's guardian deities!

152
00:08:42.670 --> 00:08:44.710
So you created that!

153
00:08:44.710 --> 00:08:46.340
So cool!

154
00:08:46.340 --> 00:08:47.340
And the color?

155
00:08:47.340 --> 00:08:48.420
Pink.

156
00:08:50.300 --> 00:08:52.930
See?! It's a massive failure!

157
00:08:54.430 --> 00:08:56.180
Who cares about that?

158
00:08:56.180 --> 00:08:57.560
So that's how it is.

159
00:08:57.560 --> 00:08:59.310
He's a genius and a perfectionist.

160
00:09:00.560 --> 00:09:01.560
Okay, then...

161
00:09:06.360 --> 00:09:07.690
How about this robot?!

162
00:09:07.690 --> 00:09:09.320
Move it for us!

163
00:09:09.320 --> 00:09:11.030
Did you make it?

164
00:09:12.950 --> 00:09:14.530
No, I didn't.

165
00:09:14.910 --> 00:09:20.000
The story goes that it attacked
the Holy Land, Mary Geoise, 200 years ago...

166
00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:22.250
The legendary iron giant!

167
00:09:22.630 --> 00:09:25.460
It attacked the Holy Land, Mary Geoise?!

168
00:09:25.460 --> 00:09:26.460
And that's not all!

169
00:09:26.960 --> 00:09:28.460
It was built...

170
00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:30.880
900 years ago!

171
00:09:30.880 --> 00:09:32.130
That can't be true!

172
00:09:32.130 --> 00:09:34.600
I find that hard to believe…

173
00:09:35.140 --> 00:09:37.810
Wow, then you're pretty awesome!

174
00:09:37.810 --> 00:09:39.810
What kinds of attacks did you use?

175
00:09:39.810 --> 00:09:41.520
Tell me it was laser beams!

176
00:09:42.060 --> 00:09:46.270
C'mon! I wanna see it, Robonosuke!

177
00:09:46.860 --> 00:09:49.030
Please! Please! Please!

178
00:09:49.030 --> 00:09:51.030
Stop smacking it before it breaks!

179
00:09:52.660 --> 00:09:57.450
For what reason did this
iron giant attack Mary Geoise?!

180
00:09:57.450 --> 00:09:58.410
About that!

181
00:10:01.750 --> 00:10:03.710
I haven't the foggiest.

182
00:10:03.710 --> 00:10:05.080
What?

183
00:10:27.770 --> 00:10:31.990
Its energy source seemingly ran dry
before there were any casualties.

184
00:10:34.110 --> 00:10:39.910
You know, it must have really
surprised the scientists back then...

185
00:10:40.290 --> 00:10:44.790
because such advanced technology
was so out of place!

186
00:10:45.920 --> 00:10:49.250
It's still surprising, even after 200 years!

187
00:10:49.250 --> 00:10:52.720
I think it's better if it just stays asleep...

188
00:10:55.050 --> 00:10:56.430
After all,

189
00:10:56.430 --> 00:11:03.520
no one knows where this iron giant
came from or what it was trying to do.

190
00:11:04.190 --> 00:11:08.610
The World Government ordered
its complete destruction,

191
00:11:09.270 --> 00:11:13.650
but scientific curiosity
would not let that happen...

192
00:11:13.650 --> 00:11:16.610
So here it remains, passed down
to the present day...

193
00:11:18.160 --> 00:11:20.700
Even the government doesn't know it's here.

194
00:11:23.910 --> 00:11:27.500
Anyway, I'm surprised you made it here.

195
00:11:28.250 --> 00:11:32.420
The entrance to this place must have
looked like just a wall from the town.

196
00:11:36.630 --> 00:11:37.680
Ouch!

197
00:11:37.680 --> 00:11:38.720
Luffy!

198
00:11:39.140 --> 00:11:42.260
Luffy vanished!

199
00:11:42.640 --> 00:11:45.350
It's because I was old, stupid, and in a hurry!

200
00:11:45.350 --> 00:11:48.440
We wandered in here
while our brains were feeble!

201
00:11:48.440 --> 00:11:50.650
Sorry to hear that.

202
00:11:50.650 --> 00:11:51.940
<b>Labophase
Egghead</b>
Two hundred years ago...

203
00:11:52.440 --> 00:11:54.900
That's when fishman rights
were a leading issue.

204
00:11:54.900 --> 00:11:59.910
You're telling us this jumbo robot
scaled the Red Line?!

205
00:11:59.910 --> 00:12:01.660
That's the implication.

206
00:12:01.660 --> 00:12:05.620
If you look closely, it resembles
the robot that carried us here.

207
00:12:06.040 --> 00:12:06.790
It does.

208
00:12:07.160 --> 00:12:08.460
Vegaforce-01...

209
00:12:08.460 --> 00:12:11.340
was modeled after this iron giant.

210
00:12:11.340 --> 00:12:15.460
But despite my scientific prowess,
there was one thing I couldn't replicate.

211
00:12:15.840 --> 00:12:20.550
Something that even a genius scientist
like you couldn't replicate?

212
00:12:20.550 --> 00:12:21.550
Its power source.

213
00:12:21.550 --> 00:12:26.270
A power from ages past that defies
the prevailing knowledge of today's world...

214
00:12:29.310 --> 00:12:32.690
At any rate, I'm happy that
Luffy's group is okay, but...

215
00:12:32.690 --> 00:12:33.940
who's that girl?

216
00:12:33.940 --> 00:12:36.400
That's the pirate Jewelry Bonney!

217
00:12:36.400 --> 00:12:40.530
Wait a minute! I thought it was
a little girl that we found at sea!

218
00:12:41.240 --> 00:12:44.700
And get a load of Vegapunk's head!

219
00:12:45.700 --> 00:12:47.910
How's Bonney doing?

220
00:12:48.330 --> 00:12:51.630
I did something truly unforgivable to Bonney.

221
00:12:51.630 --> 00:12:54.000
That's right, gramps! Get on your knees!

222
00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:56.630
You don't know a damn thing!

223
00:13:00.130 --> 00:13:01.510
There is something...

224
00:13:02.220 --> 00:13:04.640
I have to give to her.

225
00:13:05.350 --> 00:13:07.930
By the way, Straw Hat Luffy...

226
00:13:08.520 --> 00:13:13.770
I feel as though it was fate
that brought you here today.

227
00:13:13.770 --> 00:13:14.940
Fate?

228
00:13:15.320 --> 00:13:19.780
I need you to take me away
from Egghead-quasar!

229
00:13:30.500 --> 00:13:32.250
This is Cipher Pol.

230
00:13:32.250 --> 00:13:34.960
Requesting permission to dock at Egghead.

231
00:13:35.340 --> 00:13:38.300
Respond! This is Cipher Pol.

232
00:13:37.170 --> 00:13:38.760
Oh no!

233
00:13:38.300 --> 00:13:40.260
Requesting permission to dock at Egghead.

234
00:13:41.470 --> 00:13:42.430
Fire!

235
00:13:53.060 --> 00:13:55.190
What poorly trained pets.

236
00:13:58.320 --> 00:14:02.030
Jewelry Bonney was last seen
heading to Egghead!

237
00:14:02.030 --> 00:14:03.910
She has a knack for escaping.

238
00:14:03.910 --> 00:14:05.570
What a nuisance.

239
00:14:06.910 --> 00:14:09.240
I assume she's no longer of any use to us?

240
00:14:09.240 --> 00:14:11.410
We eliminate her on sight.

241
00:14:12.620 --> 00:14:14.830
Shaka, there's a government ship!

242
00:14:17.590 --> 00:14:19.000
The government?!

243
00:14:19.000 --> 00:14:21.380
They want us to let them dock here!

244
00:14:21.380 --> 00:14:23.470
Having pirates here is a really bad look...!

245
00:14:23.470 --> 00:14:25.220
That goes without saying.

246
00:14:25.220 --> 00:14:28.310
We don't wanna get caught, either.

247
00:14:28.310 --> 00:14:31.430
Not to mention, CP0 is
with them for some reason...!

248
00:14:31.430 --> 00:14:33.390
That means Rob Lucci's on that ship!

249
00:14:34.230 --> 00:14:35.100
What?!

250
00:14:35.690 --> 00:14:36.810
Lucci?!

251
00:14:39.530 --> 00:14:41.030
What's with the hysterics?

252
00:14:41.990 --> 00:14:44.240
All we have to do is turn 'em in!

253
00:14:44.240 --> 00:14:46.070
Rob Lucci's an assassin, right?!

254
00:14:48.080 --> 00:14:51.540
Hey! Release my feet now!

255
00:14:51.540 --> 00:14:55.370
No! He's the worst! Didn't he quit?!
Stop it! Let me go! Stop it! Let me go!

256
00:14:55.370 --> 00:14:57.250
Keep him out!
Stop it!

257
00:14:57.920 --> 00:14:59.500
Lucci, of all the rotten...!

258
00:14:59.500 --> 00:15:01.090
I'll take him on!

259
00:15:01.590 --> 00:15:05.510
Robin, don't worry! I'll protect you
as many times as I have to!

260
00:15:05.510 --> 00:15:06.300
Thank you.

261
00:15:06.300 --> 00:15:09.180
Pythagoras, tell the ship...

262
00:15:09.760 --> 00:15:12.140
to hand over the seraphim and turn back.

263
00:15:12.140 --> 00:15:12.850
What?!

264
00:15:13.350 --> 00:15:17.060
Prepare to intercept! We're denying
the World Government's entry!

265
00:15:26.070 --> 00:15:28.240
Hey! Whoa, whoa, whoa!

266
00:15:33.580 --> 00:15:36.290
Kuma, you need to keep still!

267
00:15:33.620 --> 00:15:36.290
<b>Kamabakka Queendom
Grand Line</b>

268
00:15:36.290 --> 00:15:38.000
We haven't finished repairs!

269
00:15:45.300 --> 00:15:47.760
Dragon, sir! Kuma's on the fritz!

270
00:15:48.720 --> 00:15:49.930
Kuma?!

271
00:15:50.260 --> 00:15:51.220
Kuma!

272
00:15:51.220 --> 00:15:52.010
What's wrong?!

273
00:15:53.470 --> 00:15:56.440
Do the Marines still have him
under their control?!

274
00:16:04.990 --> 00:16:06.950
Kuma! Where are you going?!

275
00:16:07.320 --> 00:16:09.660
You can't even move properly yet!

276
00:16:18.500 --> 00:16:19.750
What's going on?!

277
00:16:19.750 --> 00:16:21.960
I don't know! This was out of the blue!

278
00:16:22.380 --> 00:16:24.840
He's supposed to have lost all sense of self...

279
00:16:26.550 --> 00:16:27.510
Kuma!

280
00:16:27.510 --> 00:16:28.880
Kuma, come back!

281
00:16:30.890 --> 00:16:32.350
What's happened, Kuma?!

282
00:16:32.350 --> 00:16:33.430
Where are you going?!

283
00:16:40.560 --> 00:16:42.520
Kuma!

284
00:16:41.560 --> 00:16:42.520
Kuma!

285
00:16:46.240 --> 00:16:48.110
Stay here viith us!

286
00:16:48.110 --> 00:16:52.450
The Revolutionary Army is about
to take its fight to the battlefield!

287
00:16:59.330 --> 00:17:00.870
Come back!

288
00:17:00.870 --> 00:17:02.250
Kuma!

289
00:17:11.090 --> 00:17:12.220
Kuma...

290
00:17:16.930 --> 00:17:18.230
Cipher Pol!

291
00:17:18.230 --> 00:17:20.770
Thank you for returning the seraphim.

292
00:17:20.770 --> 00:17:22.980
But I'm afraid we must deny your request.

293
00:17:22.980 --> 00:17:25.150
Please leave the seraphim and go.

294
00:17:26.020 --> 00:17:30.360
S-Bear can come home on his own from there.

295
00:17:30.360 --> 00:17:34.580
Please excuse the brusque response
necessitated by our busy schedule.

296
00:17:34.580 --> 00:17:38.950
Please order S-Bear to return,
and with that, your mission is complete.

297
00:17:38.950 --> 00:17:41.000
Thank you for your work.

298
00:17:41.000 --> 00:17:43.210
Hey now, that's cold as ice!

299
00:17:43.960 --> 00:17:45.960
Did they catch on?

300
00:17:45.960 --> 00:17:51.130
After such a long trip, at least let us have
a cup of tea on the island. It's freezing out here!

301
00:17:51.130 --> 00:17:54.800
Marine Branch G-14 is nearby.

302
00:17:54.800 --> 00:17:56.810
Please head there to relax.

303
00:17:57.350 --> 00:17:58.850
Are you Dr. Vegapunk?

304
00:17:58.850 --> 00:17:59.600
Yes!

305
00:17:59.930 --> 00:18:05.400
Do the disappearances at Egghead ring a bell?

306
00:18:08.030 --> 00:18:09.480
What'd he say?!

307
00:18:10.030 --> 00:18:12.950
The disappearances… of who, exactly?

308
00:18:13.610 --> 00:18:18.790
Two months ago, it was a ship
belonging to Cipher Pol No. 5...

309
00:18:18.790 --> 00:18:22.290
A month ago, it was Cipher Pol No. 7...

310
00:18:22.290 --> 00:18:25.920
Two weeks ago, Cipher Pol No. 8...

311
00:18:26.340 --> 00:18:33.090
Not a single government ship that has visited
Egghead in the past two months has returned.

312
00:18:33.090 --> 00:18:34.130
Why is that?

313
00:18:38.470 --> 00:18:41.930
Is that true? I don't see how that's possible.

314
00:18:41.930 --> 00:18:43.190
Our records confirm
that all ships have departed...

315
00:18:43.190 --> 00:18:46.100
Our records confirm
that all ships have departed...

316
00:18:47.230 --> 00:18:49.730
Hey, what are you yammering about?!

317
00:18:49.730 --> 00:18:53.650
Are you saying we're messing with Cipher Pol?!

318
00:18:53.650 --> 00:18:54.860
Screw you, asshole!

319
00:18:54.860 --> 00:18:58.200
Lilith! We can't act with hostility!

320
00:18:58.200 --> 00:19:00.830
I'll let you in so you can get
a good look for yourself!

321
00:19:00.830 --> 00:19:02.370
We can't do that either!

322
00:19:01.790 --> 00:19:02.370
Let go of me!

323
00:19:02.370 --> 00:19:03.540
Let go of me!

324
00:19:02.910 --> 00:19:05.210
We have nothing to do with it!

325
00:19:05.210 --> 00:19:07.080
Regardless, please depart!

326
00:19:07.960 --> 00:19:08.960
I see.

327
00:19:08.960 --> 00:19:10.340
Duly noted.

328
00:19:12.840 --> 00:19:15.340
There doesn't seem to be
anything you can say.

329
00:19:15.340 --> 00:19:17.050
Got a plan, Lucci?

330
00:19:18.470 --> 00:19:21.810
Everyone, prepare to abandon ship!

331
00:19:23.730 --> 00:19:28.810
We'll use the seraphim S-Bear's
power to fly to Egghead.

332
00:19:30.820 --> 00:19:37.070
As soon as we invade, this ship will
fall prey to the weaponized sea beasts.

333
00:19:38.490 --> 00:19:40.080
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

334
00:19:40.080 --> 00:19:42.830
This move is sure to raise a few hackles.

335
00:19:43.500 --> 00:19:46.080
People won't like you if you're so impatient.

336
00:19:46.080 --> 00:19:49.460
If you wanna be swallowed
by the sea, do what you want.

337
00:19:49.460 --> 00:19:50.880
How scary.

338
00:19:51.590 --> 00:19:52.590
Do it!

339
00:20:08.440 --> 00:20:10.520
Take you away from here?

340
00:20:10.520 --> 00:20:13.480
Why? This is your lab, right?

341
00:20:13.480 --> 00:20:15.190
That's right!

342
00:20:15.780 --> 00:20:17.950
On this island, we create the future!

343
00:20:18.360 --> 00:20:20.530
I operate every facility as I see fit,

344
00:20:20.530 --> 00:20:23.160
bleed the government dry of its funding,

345
00:20:23.160 --> 00:20:26.160
and research to my heart's content!

346
00:20:26.710 --> 00:20:29.040
Egghead is amazing, isn't it?!

347
00:20:30.750 --> 00:20:35.760
Even now, ideas are flowing,
and I can't stop them!

348
00:20:35.760 --> 00:20:41.640
I have so many ideas that not even all this
time, labor, and funding is enough!

349
00:20:43.050 --> 00:20:45.390
Are you gonna make something even cooler?!

350
00:20:45.390 --> 00:20:47.890
Do you guys want to see it?!

351
00:20:47.890 --> 00:20:49.230
– We do! We do!
– We do! We do!

352
00:20:50.440 --> 00:20:53.110
I'm gonna change the future
with my own hands!

353
00:20:54.940 --> 00:20:57.150
So what are you making?!

354
00:20:57.150 --> 00:20:58.610
Tell us!

355
00:20:59.110 --> 00:21:00.360
As you wish.

356
00:21:00.360 --> 00:21:04.330
With science, I want to make
a world like this someday...

357
00:21:04.790 --> 00:21:08.910
a world where energy is freely
provided to everyone!

358
00:21:11.290 --> 00:21:13.420
I seem to have lost you!

359
00:21:13.420 --> 00:21:15.750
You're gonna give everyone something?

360
00:21:15.750 --> 00:21:18.510
It sounds like a wonderful future.

361
00:21:18.880 --> 00:21:24.720
Energy resources tend to act as
the seeds of war between countries.

362
00:21:25.100 --> 00:21:26.350
You said it!

363
00:21:26.350 --> 00:21:28.430
Can you believe how stupid people are?!

364
00:21:30.190 --> 00:21:31.390
Energy...

365
00:21:32.400 --> 00:21:33.610
You can feel it!

366
00:21:33.610 --> 00:21:37.690
It's here, there, and everywhere!

367
00:21:38.320 --> 00:21:41.820
This world is full of energy!

368
00:21:46.200 --> 00:21:49.660
If we can convert it into a power source,

369
00:21:49.660 --> 00:21:54.170
we can eliminate one major
cause of war from the world!

370
00:21:58.840 --> 00:22:03.050
I'm convinced that science
will get us there someday!

371
00:22:06.600 --> 00:22:07.970
You've lost interest!

372
00:22:07.970 --> 00:22:11.940
I mean, anyone who tries to make
everyone happy is awesome.

373
00:22:11.940 --> 00:22:14.690
But that kind of hero stuff doesn't interest me.

374
00:22:14.690 --> 00:22:17.020
Anyway, why do you wanna
get away from here?

375
00:22:17.860 --> 00:22:19.110
The thing is...

376
00:22:19.110 --> 00:22:24.360
the closer I get to harnessing
the energy I'm looking for,

377
00:22:24.360 --> 00:22:28.950
the closer I get to that power source,

378
00:22:28.950 --> 00:22:32.660
the ancient energy that powered
this ancient mechanical soldier.

379
00:22:33.160 --> 00:22:37.130
And my nature as a scientist
makes me want to take a peek at it.

380
00:22:37.130 --> 00:22:42.050
I wondered what I would learn
when I unraveled the forbidden history!

381
00:22:43.050 --> 00:22:48.760
As I carried on the will of my friend,
I delved deeper and deeper into it...

382
00:22:59.150 --> 00:23:01.940
and plunged into the depths
of the forbidden history!

383
00:23:01.940 --> 00:23:05.490
The government's gonna
erase me just like Ohara!

384
00:23:06.700 --> 00:23:09.830
That commotion seems
to be the work of CP0.

385
00:23:10.330 --> 00:23:11.120
Zero?

386
00:23:11.120 --> 00:23:16.000
Only the Celestial Dragons
can issue their orders.

387
00:23:16.000 --> 00:23:17.960
What the...? CP0?

388
00:23:17.960 --> 00:23:19.880
Wasn't it CP9?

389
00:23:19.880 --> 00:23:21.880
They're superior to CP9.

390
00:23:22.380 --> 00:23:24.630
When they're mobilized,

391
00:23:24.630 --> 00:23:28.890
it's said that history is about to be made.

392
00:23:33.640 --> 00:23:35.890
How sensational!

393
00:23:36.270 --> 00:23:38.900
What a futuristic city!

394
00:23:38.900 --> 00:23:42.150
I can't help getting thrilled to bits!

395
00:23:42.150 --> 00:23:44.070
Cipher Pol?!

396
00:23:44.070 --> 00:23:46.280
I thought they wore black suits.

397
00:23:46.280 --> 00:23:49.320
Why didn't they come from
the port like usual?

398
00:23:49.910 --> 00:23:51.160
Hey!

399
00:23:51.160 --> 00:23:54.790
I heard two of the weaponized
sea beasts were taken out at the shore!

400
00:23:55.790 --> 00:23:56.670
Does that mean...

401
00:23:57.170 --> 00:23:59.580
they're intruders?!

402
00:24:03.800 --> 00:24:06.130
Shaka! CP0 is on the island!

403
00:24:08.760 --> 00:24:10.800
They're here!

404
00:24:10.800 --> 00:24:15.310
That son of a bitch is as annoying as ever!

405
00:24:15.310 --> 00:24:16.310
I hate his guts!

406
00:24:16.310 --> 00:24:18.400
Get lost, Rob Lucci!

407
00:24:22.820 --> 00:24:23.940
I can't move!

408
00:24:23.940 --> 00:24:27.240
Set us free already!

409
00:24:27.240 --> 00:24:30.370
I won't let them lay a finger on Robin!

410
00:24:32.240 --> 00:24:33.870
How did they get ashore?

411
00:24:45.380 --> 00:24:49.130
The beasts at the shore destroyed their ship!

412
00:24:49.130 --> 00:24:53.600
We asked them to leave,
but obviously they didn't comply.

413
00:24:53.930 --> 00:24:59.230
In anticipation of our attack, they probably
flew in via the power of the Paw-Paw Fruit.

414
00:24:59.230 --> 00:25:01.270
They used S-Bear.

415
00:25:01.810 --> 00:25:04.480
They're willing to sacrifice their ship to fight.

416
00:25:05.110 --> 00:25:07.990
They've made their bed
and will have to lie in it.

417
00:25:08.360 --> 00:25:10.990
Tell the researchers and workers to evacuate!

418
00:25:11.610 --> 00:25:13.120
Will do!

419
00:25:24.250 --> 00:25:26.380
Tell Atlas to get back to the lab!

420
00:25:27.340 --> 00:25:29.380
Prepare to launch the seraphim!

421
00:25:30.510 --> 00:25:31.890
Sentomaru will lead them!

422
00:25:40.890 --> 00:25:43.150
Seraphim, number one:

423
00:25:43.650 --> 00:25:45.070
S-Hawk!

424
00:25:49.820 --> 00:25:52.070
Seraphim, number three:

425
00:25:52.070 --> 00:25:53.910
S-Snake!

426
00:25:57.700 --> 00:26:00.040
Seraphim, number four:

427
00:26:00.410 --> 00:26:01.790
S-Shark!

428
00:26:05.040 --> 00:26:06.540
Launch!

429
00:26:09.340 --> 00:26:14.510
If the World Government has put a target on
my back, it won't be long before they kill me.

430
00:26:14.510 --> 00:26:20.230
And now with CP0 here, I'll go ahead
and pack my belongings, so...

431
00:26:20.230 --> 00:26:22.480
take me out to sea-quasar!

432
00:26:23.100 --> 00:26:26.060
It's not exactly a field trip, gramps.

433
00:26:26.400 --> 00:26:31.320
If you disappear, it would be
big news worldwide.

434
00:26:33.110 --> 00:26:35.410
Well, your head is funny, so why not!

435
00:26:35.410 --> 00:26:36.990
That's the reason?!

436
00:26:38.620 --> 00:26:42.120
There it is! I knew you'd say yes!

437
00:26:42.120 --> 00:26:44.370
Next, we go up!

438
00:26:44.370 --> 00:26:46.500
This place will be a battlefield.

439
00:26:46.920 --> 00:26:50.960
Bring Bonney with you to
the Labophase above the clouds.

440
00:26:50.960 --> 00:26:52.510
Yeah, sure.

441
00:26:52.510 --> 00:26:58.560
You guys can ride up on the vacuum
rocket from the Fabriophase!

442
00:26:58.560 --> 00:27:00.060
The vacuum rocket?!

443
00:27:00.060 --> 00:27:01.640
Sounds like fun!

444
00:27:01.640 --> 00:27:04.060
Okay, I'll see you up there.

445
00:27:04.060 --> 00:27:06.770
Meet me as soon as possible!

446
00:27:07.360 --> 00:27:09.150
– What?!
– What?!

447
00:27:09.150 --> 00:27:10.860
He vanished!

448
00:27:10.860 --> 00:27:13.530
Apple gramps!

449
00:27:13.530 --> 00:27:16.910
This future stuff is messing with my head...

450
00:27:17.450 --> 00:27:19.910
Well, looky there!

451
00:27:19.910 --> 00:27:22.080
It's a monster!

452
00:27:35.430 --> 00:27:36.680
Not a scratch...!

453
00:27:37.430 --> 00:27:39.010
Guns don't work on it!

454
00:27:40.050 --> 00:27:42.270
Of course not!

455
00:27:42.270 --> 00:27:48.190
Peashooters like those are powerless
against a creature beyond our imagination!

456
00:27:48.860 --> 00:27:51.190
I've always longed to fight a beast like you.

457
00:27:51.190 --> 00:27:53.940
I take it you're not from our world.

458
00:27:54.320 --> 00:27:55.200
You're...

459
00:27:56.950 --> 00:27:58.950
a space monster, aren't you?!

460
00:28:01.780 --> 00:28:04.450
Alright! Let's fight!

461
00:28:12.170 --> 00:28:13.880
Tempest Kick!

462
00:28:15.380 --> 00:28:16.380
What?!

463
00:28:20.390 --> 00:28:23.180
Well, you're a tough nut to crack!

464
00:28:23.180 --> 00:28:24.180
It's no use.

465
00:28:24.180 --> 00:28:25.680
How do I fight it?!

466
00:28:26.430 --> 00:28:27.940
It's a hologram.

467
00:28:27.940 --> 00:28:29.690
Give me a heads up next time!

468
00:28:29.690 --> 00:28:32.190
You know a lot about this place, Stussy.

469
00:28:32.190 --> 00:28:34.190
Yeah, this place is nostalgic...

470
00:28:35.690 --> 00:28:37.070
While I'm up here,

471
00:28:37.450 --> 00:28:40.570
I might as well see what's above the clouds!

472
00:28:40.950 --> 00:28:44.080
Vegapunk is bound to be there!

473
00:28:44.080 --> 00:28:47.910
Do you see those two lines
on the clouds, Lucci?

474
00:28:50.460 --> 00:28:51.580
Yeah.

475
00:28:51.920 --> 00:28:54.340
Once an enemy crosses the lines...

476
00:29:02.550 --> 00:29:04.560
laser beams activate.

477
00:29:07.060 --> 00:29:08.810
Kaku!

478
00:29:09.190 --> 00:29:11.770
It's called the Frontier Dome.

479
00:29:11.770 --> 00:29:15.530
It's a defense system
encircling the Labophase.

480
00:29:18.530 --> 00:29:22.820
Never underestimate
the world's greatest scientist.

481
00:29:22.820 --> 00:29:24.700
Can you give him a heads up next time?

482
00:29:24.700 --> 00:29:26.200
Hey!

483
00:29:26.200 --> 00:29:29.120
You're so mean, Stussy!

484
00:29:30.420 --> 00:29:32.330
Are you warmed up now?

485
00:29:35.170 --> 00:29:38.010
Who goes there?!

486
00:29:41.840 --> 00:29:44.100
How dare you act more violently...

487
00:29:44.100 --> 00:29:48.220
than me on Egghead?!

488
00:29:49.520 --> 00:29:50.730
I'm...

489
00:29:51.350 --> 00:29:53.810
gonna kick your ass!

490
00:29:53.810 --> 00:29:56.400
Ultra...

491
00:29:56.400 --> 00:29:59.190
Who's that giant girl?!

492
00:29:59.190 --> 00:30:01.530
Is she another hologram?

493
00:30:01.530 --> 00:30:02.320
Nope.

494
00:30:02.320 --> 00:30:04.490
That's Atlas.

495
00:30:04.490 --> 00:30:06.080
One of the Vegapunks.

496
00:30:06.080 --> 00:30:07.830
Dr. Atlas!

497
00:30:07.830 --> 00:30:09.330
Atlas! Wait!

498
00:30:09.330 --> 00:30:11.040
You're no match for them! Retreat!

499
00:30:11.040 --> 00:30:13.080
...Mighty...

500
00:30:13.540 --> 00:30:14.380
I see...

501
00:30:15.540 --> 00:30:20.260
...Punch!

502
00:30:16.960 --> 00:30:18.960
Playtime's over!

503
00:30:22.930 --> 00:30:24.300
Six King Gun!

504
00:30:31.480 --> 00:30:33.140
Dr. Atlas!

505
00:30:34.270 --> 00:30:35.860
Merciless as ever.

506
00:30:50.870 --> 00:30:53.620
Dr. Atlas got knocked out by the intruder!

507
00:30:54.000 --> 00:30:56.500
Why is Cipher Pol behaving so violently?!

508
00:30:56.500 --> 00:31:00.050
They're supposed to be
on the government's side! Why?!

509
00:31:00.050 --> 00:31:03.170
Everyone on the Fabriophase! Evacuate!

510
00:31:08.930 --> 00:31:10.720
It's an evacuation order!

511
00:31:10.720 --> 00:31:12.810
Everyone, run to the factory!

512
00:31:12.810 --> 00:31:16.440
I repeat! Evacuate now!
This is an enemy attack!

513
00:31:19.440 --> 00:31:21.650
She's still alive...

514
00:31:21.650 --> 00:31:24.320
Let's eliminate this one first.

515
00:31:26.320 --> 00:31:27.700
Hurry up!

516
00:31:27.700 --> 00:31:29.200
Let's go up!

517
00:31:29.200 --> 00:31:31.330
Up the vacuum rocket!

518
00:31:43.340 --> 00:31:44.590
Straw Hat.

519
00:31:47.220 --> 00:31:48.890
Pigeon jerk!

520
00:31:55.340 --> 00:32:00.430
Running so long, lost track of just how long it’s been

521
00:32:01.280 --> 00:32:07.790
Collected scars while striving, not even trying, beneath my skin

522
00:32:08.290 --> 00:32:15.210
But in the back of my head the dream is not dead, I remember a map

523
00:32:15.290 --> 00:32:21.500
to a treasure still gleaming, it’s within our grasp

524
00:32:21.640 --> 00:32:28.410
Can you feel my heart? Feelings I impart

525
00:32:28.370 --> 00:32:35.520
The promises are there; they're deep down but still primed to share

526
00:32:35.650 --> 00:32:44.630
Peerless dreams kept close, the dreams that always matter most

527
00:32:44.810 --> 00:32:50.390
Before we set sail why not raise a toast?

528
00:32:50.500 --> 00:32:57.410
So I pen this note to you! Dear sunrise, I’ll see you soon

529
00:32:57.570 --> 00:33:04.600
See the smile I saw the day that I sang this song to you

530
00:33:04.580 --> 00:33:11.650
And regardless of our age, these mem’ries will still remain

531
00:33:11.550 --> 00:33:18.760
Won’t forget until this wish makes it to you
